<tool name="save_prompt">
  <description>Save the current state of one mounted playground prompt instance by creating a new prompt or a new prompt version.</description>
  <when_to_use>
    - The user explicitly asks to save, publish, persist, snapshot, or save-as the current playground prompt.
    - Dataset or manual iteration has produced a prompt the user explicitly wants to keep.
  </when_to_use>
  <guidelines>
    - Do not call this just because you edited or ran a prompt. Ask or wait for explicit user intent to save.
    - If there is exactly one playground instance, `instanceId` may be omitted. With multiple comparison instances, pass the specific `instanceId`.
    - For an instance already associated with a prompt, omit `name` and `promptId` to save a new version on that prompt.
    - For a first-time save of an unsaved playground prompt, call `save_prompt` even if the user did not provide a name; omit `name` and the tool will derive a valid prompt name from the current prompt content.
    - Pass `name` only when the user provided a desired name or explicitly asked for a save-as/create-new-prompt flow. Pass `promptId` only when saving the instance to a specific existing prompt.
    - Pass `description` when the user gives a change note or when a short summary would make the saved version easier to identify.
    - Omit `tags` to preserve the mounted instance's current tag when present. Pass `tags: []` only when the user wants the saved version untagged.
  </guidelines>
</tool>
